 to run the GUI with normal docker you must

 build :

   docker build -t et .

run:

   docker run --rm   --gpus all   -e DISPLAY=$DISPLAY   -v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix   et

on my laptop i had to run this for it to run:

   docker run --rm -it \
      --gpus all \
      --device /dev/dri \
      --env NVIDIA_DRIVER_CAPABILITIES=graphics,utility,compute \
      --env DISPLAY=$DISPLAY \
      --volume /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix \
   et


if your on linux you must configure 

xhost +local:docker

i dont use windows or mac so i dont know if it will run out of the gate, 

to compile shaders use 

chmod +x compile.sh

./compile.sh



To create the engine i followed a tutorial by "Brendan Galea" so thanks to him for that
